{
  "text": "In the early 1990's, BST-1 was described as a surface antigen expressed by human bone marrow stromal cells [CITATION_1] , not knowing that BST-1 was identical to the antigen Mo5 identified a decade earlier in the myeloid lineage [CITATION_2] . In the VI Workshop on Differentiation Antigens, BST-1 and Mo5 were univocally designated as CD157 [CITATION_3] .",
